  "informal_statement": "For every real t ≥ 2, (t − 1) log 2 − log(t + 2) − 2√t · log t ≤ θ(t): the natural-number Chebyshev lower bound transfers to a fully real-valued form usable inside integrals.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Combine the primorial-based lower bound for θ at natural arguments with explicit floor bracketing, absorbing the rounding loss into the −log(t+2) − 2√t·log t correction terms so the inequality holds pointwise for all real t ≥ 2.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem theta_real_lower_bridge :\n    ∀ t : ℝ, 2 ≤ t → (t - 1) * Real.log 2 - Real.log (t + 2) - 2 * Real.sqrt t * Real.log t ≤ Chebyshev.theta t",
